==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tribolet
<hw>Trib"o*let</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos>} <ety>[F. <ets>triboulet</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A goldsmith's tool used in making rings.</def>
<rj><au>Ainsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A steel cylinder round which metal is drawn in the
process of forming tubes.</def> <rj><au>Tomlinson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Blacksmithing)</fld> <def>A tapering
mandrel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>tribo-</ent>⟦br⟧
